Privacy Policy for Curio
Effective Date: [Insert Date]

Curio ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting the privacy and personal information of our users ("you"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our mobile application ("App").

By accessing or using Curio, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms, please do not use the app.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:

Personal Information: Information you voluntarily provide such as name, email, gender, age, preferences, photos, or other identifying details.

Usage Data: Details of your interaction with the app, such as pages visited, features used, and session duration.

Device Information: Technical data including device type, OS version, device identifiers, and IP address.

2. How We Use Your Information
We may use your information to:

Provide and improve app functionality

Facilitate matching and social features

Personalize your experience

Communicate updates, offers, or important information

Monitor and analyze usage trends

Ensure user safety and comply with legal obligations

3. Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell your personal data. We may share your information only under the following circumstances:

With Your Consent: When you explicitly consent to sharing (e.g., matching or messaging).

Service Providers: With third-party vendors to support our operations (e.g., hosting, analytics).

Legal Compliance: When required to comply with applicable laws or legal processes.

Protection of Rights: To protect the rights, safety, and property of Curio or its users.

4. User Responsibility and Interactions
Curio provides a platform for users to connect, match, and interact. While we take reasonable steps to maintain a safe and respectful environment, we do not guarantee the behavior or intentions of any user.

You acknowledge that any communications or meetings with other users are at your sole discretion and risk, and Curio shall not be held liable for any personal, emotional, financial, or physical harm, disputes, or incidents arising out of such interactions.

We encourage all users to act responsibly, follow safety guidelines, and report any suspicious behavior.

5. Data Security
We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your data. However, no system can be 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.

6. Your Choices
You have the right to:

Access and update your personal information

Delete your account and data

Opt out of marketing communications

To exercise these rights, you may contact us at [Insert Email or Support Info].

